WEBVTT

00:11.187 --> 00:13.353
Thinking about getting
my hair cut short.

00:13.355 --> 00:14.588
That so?
Real short.

00:14.590 --> 00:16.857
So I could take my cap
on and off, like you can.

00:16.859 --> 00:18.058
Uh-huh.

00:18.060 --> 00:19.860
No more pinning it up
and sticking it in there.

00:19.862 --> 00:21.195
That's a pain.

00:21.197 --> 00:23.864
Plus a perp could grab it.
So it's also a liability.

00:23.866 --> 00:25.365
Except when
you're off duty,

00:25.367 --> 00:27.568
which is when it's just
a great head of hair.

00:27.570 --> 00:29.603
Thank you, Jamie.
And Eddie, believe me,

00:29.605 --> 00:33.040
when I say that really, truly,
that's all I got for the hair.

00:33.042 --> 00:34.975
That's more than I expected, actually.
Okay.

00:34.977 --> 00:37.177
Hey, Steve got
a new partner?

00:37.179 --> 00:40.314
Yeah, a newbie,
still on probation.

00:40.316 --> 00:43.150
Hey, Jamie, Eddie.
This is Marcus Beal.

00:43.152 --> 00:44.585
He just transferred in
from the 2-7.

00:44.587 --> 00:45.752
Hey.
Hey. Welcome.

00:45.754 --> 00:47.054
How's it going? Hey.
Nice to meet you.

00:47.056 --> 00:49.289
Give me a sec.
All right. I'll meet you out front.

00:49.291 --> 00:50.357
All right.

00:50.359 --> 00:51.625
Not wearing your vest.

00:51.627 --> 00:52.593
Yeah, I know.

00:52.595 --> 00:53.494
You should probably
go put one on.

00:53.496 --> 00:54.294
Naw, I'm good.

00:54.296 --> 00:55.529
No, go put one on.

00:55.531 --> 00:56.663
Am I missing something here?

00:56.665 --> 00:59.166
I... I thought my boss
was that Renzelli guy.

00:59.168 --> 01:00.367
Renzulli.

01:00.369 --> 01:01.935
It's department policy.
Everybody wears a vest.

01:01.937 --> 01:03.370
Policy huh?

01:03.372 --> 01:05.572
All right,
so you're one of those?

01:07.109 --> 01:08.942
Yeah, it's policy.

01:08.944 --> 01:11.945
And also, it's maybe life and
death, yours and your partner's.

01:11.947 --> 01:13.280
All right, well then,
you know...

01:13.282 --> 01:15.082
Steve can say something,
or the sarge can,

01:15.084 --> 01:17.451
but, you know, there's no policy
that says I gotta answer to you.

01:17.453 --> 01:18.619
All right?

01:23.225 --> 01:25.626
Rough Tough Creampuff.

01:25.628 --> 01:27.928
Above my pay grade.

01:27.930 --> 01:29.663
Never thought I'd actually
hear you say that.

01:29.665 --> 01:32.032
Lived and learned.

01:33.636 --> 01:34.902
Have you seen Anthony?

01:34.904 --> 01:36.503
I think he went down
to the break room.

01:36.505 --> 01:38.772
Break room? He owes me
a mountain of paperwork.

01:38.774 --> 01:39.907
You want me
to go get him?

01:39.909 --> 01:40.974
No, I'll go.

01:40.976 --> 01:43.210
And get the paperwork.
Two birds, one stone.

01:43.212 --> 01:44.912
Harry, you're not listening.

01:44.914 --> 01:46.480
Oh, no, no.
We're listening, okay?

01:46.482 --> 01:47.814
We're hearing him
loud and clear.

01:47.816 --> 01:49.283
He doesn't have
our money.

01:49.285 --> 01:50.384
I have what
you signed...

01:50.386 --> 01:51.618
I don't care
what I signed!

01:51.620 --> 01:53.053
You said the end
of the month.

01:53.055 --> 01:54.521
Come on, he's dead
to rights here.

01:54.523 --> 01:56.423
No, I told you that
I can't flip the property

01:56.425 --> 01:57.691
until after the closing.

01:57.693 --> 01:59.259
Now, you get your
profit when I flip,

01:59.261 --> 02:00.360
that's how it works.

02:00.362 --> 02:01.662
Profit?! Profit?!
That's what you signed!

02:01.664 --> 02:03.397
Forget about profit, Joe.
Forget about profit, okay?

02:03.399 --> 02:04.865
I just want
the money back.

02:04.867 --> 02:06.066
I can't believe
you vouched for this idiot.

02:06.068 --> 02:07.634
I can't believe
you forgot to tell us

02:07.636 --> 02:09.235
what a lying
scumbag he is.

02:09.238 --> 02:10.737
Okay, Harry, that's enough!
What's with the fingers, huh?!

02:10.739 --> 02:12.973
Hey!

02:12.975 --> 02:14.641
What's going on here?

02:14.643 --> 02:15.909
Small misunderstanding.

02:15.911 --> 02:17.311
100 grand ain't small.

02:17.313 --> 02:19.580
The situation's exactly
what he said it was.

02:19.582 --> 02:21.181
What is your problem?
My problem?

02:21.183 --> 02:23.150
You're ripping off cops.

02:23.152 --> 02:24.418
You got it coming.

02:24.420 --> 02:25.485
The both of you.
Oh, really?!

02:25.487 --> 02:26.753
Yeah!
Now it's a threat?!

02:26.755 --> 02:28.188
That was a threat!
You're going to threaten me?!

02:29.358 --> 02:30.724
Break it up!

02:30.726 --> 02:32.693
Both of you, upstairs.

02:38.267 --> 02:40.133
Hey. What are you doing here?

02:40.135 --> 02:41.935
Oh, I was thinking maybe
we could hit the range.

02:41.937 --> 02:44.238
You know I figured I owe you a
chance for a double or nothing.

02:44.240 --> 02:45.973
Double or nothing?
Last time was a scratch.

02:45.975 --> 02:48.275
Not a chance-- I had you
by three on the last sheet.

02:48.277 --> 02:49.776
I can't anyway.
I got plans.

02:49.778 --> 02:51.311
Plans with who, your couch?

02:52.448 --> 02:54.248
All right, fine,
whatever, rain check.

02:54.250 --> 02:56.350
You really came all the way
down here to settle a bet?

02:56.352 --> 02:57.784
Actually, no.

02:57.786 --> 03:00.754
You remember me telling you
about a Corporal Jimmy Beal?

03:00.756 --> 03:02.122
Yeah, he saved
your life in Iraq.

03:02.124 --> 03:03.023
More than once.

03:03.025 --> 03:04.124
His family's in Virginia.

03:04.126 --> 03:06.293
His widow is,
but his son's up here now.

03:06.295 --> 03:08.862
And I want you
to mentor him.

03:08.864 --> 03:10.430
Mentor him?
Yeah.

03:10.432 --> 03:12.566
He just graduated the Academy
a couple months ago.

03:12.568 --> 03:14.768
All right, well how
come me and not you?

03:14.770 --> 03:17.271
'Cause he was transferred
to your precinct.

03:17.273 --> 03:18.839
There he is right now.

03:18.841 --> 03:20.173
Hey!

03:20.175 --> 03:21.441
Uncle Danny!

03:21.443 --> 03:22.809
What are you
doing here?

03:22.811 --> 03:24.544
Just checking up on you.

03:24.546 --> 03:26.413
Marcus this
is my kid brother, Jamie.

03:26.415 --> 03:28.048
Jamie, this is Marcus.

03:29.385 --> 03:30.884
He's your brother?

03:30.886 --> 03:33.220
Oh, you two have met.

03:33.222 --> 03:35.622
Yeah.
Okay.

03:35.624 --> 03:37.824
Well, whatever the hell happened
between the two of you,

03:37.826 --> 03:40.527
let's say we take
a mulligan, okay?

03:43.599 --> 03:44.965
Okay?

03:46.168 --> 03:47.768
Okay.

03:47.770 --> 03:50.070
Okay.
Good.

