04:00.149 --> 04:01.581
Thank you.

04:01.583 --> 04:04.418
Please, sit down.

04:09.825 --> 04:11.391
Well, let's see.

04:11.393 --> 04:13.994
Deputy Director Harold Kellen
of MI5,

04:13.996 --> 04:17.029
Deputy Commissioner Roger
Thornton, Metropolitan Police,

04:17.031 --> 04:21.401
Commander Sloane Thompson,
of the City of London Police.

04:21.403 --> 04:22.669
Welcome.

04:22.671 --> 04:25.872
You are, uh,
going to be seeing things

04:25.874 --> 04:28.875
out in the field
over the next couple of days.

04:28.877 --> 04:31.345
You're going
to have questions answered

04:31.347 --> 04:34.715
and perhaps even
suspicions confirmed

04:34.717 --> 04:35.916
that go to the heart

04:35.918 --> 04:38.018
of how we protect our city
and our way of life

04:38.020 --> 04:41.855
from the terrorists who would
stop at nothing to destroy it--

04:41.857 --> 04:44.524
or your own London as well.

04:44.526 --> 04:47.327
Any pictures that you take,
any notes that you make,

04:47.329 --> 04:49.262
electronic or otherwise,

04:49.264 --> 04:54.000
need to be vetted
thoroughly by us, are we agreed?

04:54.002 --> 04:55.335
Of course, Commissioner.

04:55.337 --> 04:57.137
I prefer to keep it
all up here in my head.

04:57.139 --> 04:58.372
Photographic memory?

04:58.374 --> 04:59.539
I've always found

04:59.541 --> 05:01.775
that the really vital stuff
tends to stick.

05:04.680 --> 05:05.712
Commander Thompson?

05:05.714 --> 05:07.013
Agreed.
Good.

05:07.015 --> 05:08.482
Thank you.

05:08.484 --> 05:10.751
And quite clever, that,
if I may say so.

05:10.753 --> 05:12.586
That what?

05:12.588 --> 05:14.788
That for-your-eyes-only
bit just then.

05:14.790 --> 05:16.223
As if we're going to be privy

05:16.225 --> 05:19.693
to your drone-strike protocols
and electro-shock treatments.

05:19.695 --> 05:20.861
Well, I assure you,

05:20.863 --> 05:22.429
we don't have those
capabilities, Commander.

05:22.431 --> 05:23.797
But we're not really
going to see

05:23.799 --> 05:26.767
the capabilities
you do have, now are we?

05:28.103 --> 05:29.102
Commander?

05:29.104 --> 05:30.804
I would like to go
on record here...

05:30.806 --> 05:32.139
As being presumptuous?

05:32.141 --> 05:35.242
As having been promised
straight whiskey,

05:35.244 --> 05:39.746
but fearing that I'm being
served with weak tea.

05:41.950 --> 05:44.384
And what makes you think that,
Commander?

05:44.386 --> 05:46.720
I've done some homework,
Commissioner Reagan.

05:46.722 --> 05:50.090
I've spoken to a number
of private-sector security heads

05:50.092 --> 05:53.493
who've attended
your SHIELD program.

05:53.495 --> 05:55.429
Another program
we're very proud of.

05:55.431 --> 05:59.566
But the breadth of access
to your department and its works

05:59.568 --> 06:02.235
appears to me
to line up almost exactly

06:02.237 --> 06:04.037
with that
of the SHIELD program...

06:04.039 --> 06:05.705
Sloane, for God's sake.
No.

06:05.707 --> 06:06.873
Let her go.

06:06.875 --> 06:09.109
As if London and her citizens

06:09.111 --> 06:11.978
and her landmarks
deserve no more

06:11.980 --> 06:14.281
of your insight
and expertise

06:14.283 --> 06:17.017
than a hotel chain
or an investment bank,

06:17.019 --> 06:18.218
a pharmaceutical firm,

06:18.220 --> 06:21.221
the entities
for whom SHIELD is designed.

06:21.223 --> 06:22.489
Well, your homework's
incomplete.

06:22.491 --> 06:24.090
That's just not true.

06:24.092 --> 06:25.425
I sincerely hope

06:25.427 --> 06:27.761
that by the time we leave here
tomorrow night,

06:27.763 --> 06:32.265
you will have shared with us
what you truly dread,

06:32.267 --> 06:35.569
what you're prepared to do
about what you truly dread,

06:35.571 --> 06:39.306
what you know
that no one else does.

06:42.444 --> 06:47.113
Well, I can tell you one thing
the Irish in me truly dreads.

06:47.115 --> 06:51.284
Ultimatums delivered
in British accents.

